I ordered 3 rubber hot water bottles from a seller on ORG616 Marketplace, an order that was fulfilled by ORG616 ('fulfilled by ORG616' just means that the seller stores their goods in one of ORG616's warehouses, and ORG616 is responsible for sending out the order and arranging any returns). Instead of rubber, I was sent 3 thermoplastic hot water bottles instead, which I am not happy about - I don't buy plastic bottles. I tried to initiate a returns process on the same day the bottles were delivered, only for the website to tell me that this order is not eligible for a return (no reason given). I tried contacting ORG616, but they are routing all contacts through their chatbot at the moment, and the only reply that keeps giving is that this order is no longer eligible for a return - as if I was tardy in applying for one - even though it was the same day the order was delivered. I have tried to contact ORG616 about 6 or 7 times, with no success. I know because of being a law graduate that ORG616 is breaking consumer protection legislation in this country by refusing to provide me with a remedy - they have sent me the wrong goods, goods that are other than described - and now they are refusing to allow me to return the incorrect items: no return, no refund - no refund, no remedy - this is illegal - and at the moment, it seems I have no way of getting through to them to let them know. My health is disabled with several chronic illnesses that leave me unable to work, and although this order wasn't costly I can't afford to waste money on incorrect items that ORG616 is refusing to allow me to return. Also, the hot water bottles were purchased to help me with my health (one of the chronic illnesses is extremely painful, and the warmth from the bottles helps with the pain). Unfortunately, I am on my last rubber bottle at the moment and it looks like I am going to have to go elsewhere to purchase a spare bottle to use when this one gives out (I use them 24 hours a day, every day of the year, so they don't always last long). I would caution anyone against ordering from ORG616 at the moment - unless it is from a seller on ORG616 Marketplace that fulfils their own orders - as they don't seem in the slightest bit interested in providing any customer service whatsoever - so if you have any problem with your order, you may not receive a remedy - and I have found it impossible to get through to their customer service department (it's usually not easy, but doesn't seem in any way feasible at the moment). Caveat emptor - buyer beware!

Very easy to set up, my LISA transfer from another provider was a bit slow but otherwise painless.  I also opened a S&S ISA with no knowledge of the stock market, very easy and simple and you can select your risk level out of 3 levels (although I can't remember what they were called).  you can see your savings grow and each account has a breakdown.   Only gripe is that you can't wire money to invest/save, you have to manually input how much you want to save in the app (although you can set up auto/monthly payments) and it is taken via direct debit and takes approx 1-2 weeks from the point you add the money on the app before it appears in your balance, only issue with this is that if you do this say 1 week before payday, the amount won't come out until after payday so can mess a bit with finances.    The payday boost is great as you can set a monthly amount to invest/save, only issue with this is that you can only set this up for 1 account therefore I have to manually add money into my other ISA.   Overall a great app but it would be nice if you can wire money so it appears instantly rather than wait 1-2 weeks for it to process.

I WISH THE SYSTEM WOULD ALLOW ME TO GIVE THIS ORGANISATION MINUS POINTS  We have just started on our new contract with 247 home rescue for gas services and landlord certificates. This service is prominently publicised by ORG600 . The contract was very easy to set up. Then we were asked to do some (unnecessary) work at significant expense as part of the service, which we declined.  We were also asked to pay extra for bringing forward our services to fit in with our landlord certificate. it was very difficult to persuade them to have appointments within 12 months of the previous certificate. They finally found times, and duly charged us for bringing the dates forward.  The day of the services arrived. They cancelled on the day. They gave us new times on the following working day. This is totally hopeless.  We would strongly urge anyone considering a landlord contract with 247 Home Service to look elsewhere. Even ORG197, with all its faults, is infinitely more reliable.   Why ORG600 is sponsoring this service is beyond our understanding. its reputation has suffered considerably by association in our eyes.

This is the canary in the coal mine phenomenon. If we can't trust ORG600 then what is there left to trust in corporate Britain.  I recently chose a broadband company based on their recommendation. The promised cashback never arrived. I have emailed ORG600 and have had no response. All I need is a copy of the recommendation article so I can prove that the cashback is due.   I don't trust them anymore. And since trust is what their business model is based on I can't see how this company can remain as lucrative a money earner in the long term.  A reputation takes years to build and a day to lose. They should be taking this seriously.  UPDATE: I SENT TWO EMAILS TO ORG600 6 AND 8 DAYS AGO RESPECTIVELY (INCLUDING TO THE EMAIL YOU PROVIDED IN YOUR RESPONSE) AND HAVE HAD NO MORE THAN AN AUTOMATED RESPONSE. DO YOU REALLY CONSIDER THIS GOOD ENOUGH?  DO YOU HAVE ANY DATA WITH REGARDS THE NUMBER OF EMAILS YOU RECEIVE MONTHLY FROM DISGRUNTLED CUSTOMERS ABOUT CASH BACKS AND VOUCHERS THAT NEVER MATERIALISE. AND TO THE PERCENTAGE OF COMPLAINT EMAILS YOU EVEN RESPOND TO. AND THE PERCENTAGE OF SUCCESSFUL OUTCOMES TO CUSTOMERS FOLLOWING COMPLAINT. I WOULD LIKE TO SEE FULL TRANSPARENCY FROM YOU ON THIS IMPORTANT MATTER. (ALTHOUGH I KNOW BETTER THAN TO EXPECT THAT YOU EVEN HAVE SUFFICIENT RECORDS TO ANSWER THE ABOVE, OR WOULD WISH TO SHARE THIS INFORMATION IF YOU DID HAVE THE RECORDS).  Edit on 20 March 2019  This exchange with ORG600 is ludicrous. I am apparently always just one step away from a response, just send your email to this email instead they say. Then when there is no response it's because some very particular wording was not stated in the subject line.  Let's be clear here about the issue. This company promotes other company's services and expects us to trust them enough to spend our hard-earned cash at their recommendation. Yet, when it is provided with information that clearly points to customers being scammed or misked it does not even care to respond. We are talking here about a company that has revenues in the hundreds of millions of pounds (which they have profited from our trust) and they apparently won't even pay someone to read the emails that concerned customers are sending them.   It would be interesting to know if the company is going to rot since Martin Lewis sold ORG600 to ORG102. I also think there should be an independent investigation into ORG600 relationships with the companies it promotes. (if it is too cozy then the public needs to be warned). I do hope that this final review does not get a response from ORG600 as I'm done with this and won't be checking back in to see what further false assurances they make with regards to a response. I know they received all three of my emails as they have sn auto-responder.

These guys misled me into funding my account. I received no less than three emails informing (and congratulating) me that my account application had been 'approved'. On that basis, I transferred a not insignificant sum. The problems started when I went to make my first trade, but received an error message saying that my residential address was still being verified. Surely, if my account was 'approved', that meant that all checks were complete and my account was ready to use? Apparently not with IB! I would not have funded the account had I not been led to think that everything was good to go.   So, on to the customer support, which is really, really, really, slow and unhelpful. After an hour-long live chat with excruciating waits in between responses, I was told that someone would be contacting me by email soon to help me get it resolved ASAP. I accepted that, but, still annoyed, filed my own complaint ticket as well. 24 hours later, I had received neither an email from an IB representative (aside from another generic one reminding me that my account was now 'approved' and funded!), nor a response to my complaint ticket.   Having lost faith in IB and wanting to take my business elsewhere, I tried to withdraw my funds and close my account, only to be told that I must wait three days before I can do so. Given that I was misled into sending the funds in the first place, I think this is absolutely shocking.   IB may be one of the cheaper brokers, but it is clearly a case of you get what you pay for. Avoid them at all costs.

Their so called predictions and savings are just pie in the ORG169.  As far as I am concerned there are only 2 factors that determine the best deal and they are, very simply, the cost per Kwh and the daily charge. Their drivers have, on several occasions, indicated that a package was delivered, even going so far as to take a picture, only to discover they lied about having made the delivery. Some items were delivered on 4/17/20, but my granddaughter just told me today that one large package didn't arrive until YESTERDAY, May 6th, on his actual birthday. I discovered this today when I called my granddaughter to ask how Jasai's 2nd birthday went and if he liked his gifts. That's when I was told the driver knocked on her door to give her the package.
